  "texts": [
    "Pathology results from the biopsied mastoid tissue showed storiform fibrosis and a lymphoplasmacytic infiltration with an immunoglobulin G4 (IgG4) to IgG ratio of 48%.",
    "There was no evidence of lymphoma or plasma cell neoplasm by flow cytometry or immunohistochemistry.",
    "Serum levels of IgG4 subclass were elevated to 99.0 mg/dL (reference range: 4.0-86.0 mg/dL).",
    "He was discharged on a tapering dose of oral prednisone, and therapy with rituximab was initiated two weeks later.",
    "Six weeks after initial presentation, his ocular motility and alignment had returned to normal, and his double vision resolved completely."
  ],
